President Obama delivered a pre-recorded message to viewers of Univision's "Premio Lo Nuestro" Latin music awards show. In his message, he discussed the importance of civic participation and his commitment to expanding opportunity for all Americans. He also praised the rich diversity of Latin music and encouraged the nominees of the awards show. The message aired during the live broadcast of the show. President Obama thanked those who voted for the winners of the awards and urged everyone to stay involved and make their voices heard. He assured that he would always be listening and that his administration is working hard to reach a better day for all Americans.